kntnt-skills is a Claude Code plugin that collects Kntnt's general-purpose
skills – the ones that are useful on their own but do not belong to any of the
themed Kntnt plugins.

Made by Kntnt.

---

This product bundles third-party software:

Matt Pocock's skills (https://github.com/mattpocock/skills), licensed under the
MIT License and vendored verbatim under lib/vendor/matt-pocock/. The full licence
text and copyright notice (Copyright (c) 2026 Matt Pocock) are in
lib/vendor/matt-pocock/LICENSE. The skill-maker and plugin-maker skills build on
these files; Kntnt's own conventions on top of them are in lib/skill-conventions.md
and lib/plugin-standard.md.

---

This product is inspired by third-party work it does not bundle:

The caveman-compression concept formalised in lib/caveman.md originates with
Julius Brussee's "caveman" skill for Claude Code:
https://github.com/JuliusBrussee/caveman

The observation that a minimal rule set can outperform a long one comes from
Kuba Guzik's benchmark of that prompt:
https://github.com/kuba-guzik/caveman-micro
https://medium.com/@KubaGuzik/i-benchmarked-the-viral-caveman-prompt-to-save-llm-tokens-then-my-6-line-version-beat-it-d8e565f95e15

Kntnt's lib/caveman.md is an independent expression of these ideas, not a copy
of either author's text or code.
